# AI Command Lab — Agentic UI Module

This repo contains a **Next.js (CopilotKit + AGUI)** frontend and a **Python FastAPI (Pydantic-style)** backend
to demonstrate **agentic UI**: two-way state sync, front-end tools, and rich render directives.

## Structure

```
.
├─ next/            # Next.js + React app (Netlify)
├─ server/          # FastAPI backend (DigitalOcean / Docker)
├─ .devcontainer/   # Optional for Claude Code / VS Code dev containers
├─ netlify.toml     # Deploy config for Next.js on Netlify
└─ README.md
```

## Quick Start

### 1) Backend (FastAPI) — local
```bash
cd server
python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
cp .env.example .env
uvicorn app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload
```

### 2) Frontend (Next.js) — local
```bash
cd next
npm install
cp .env.local.example .env.local
npm run dev
```

Open: http://localhost:3000/lab/agentic-ui  
Backend default: http://localhost:8000

## Deploy

- **Frontend**: Netlify (connect GitHub → select root `netlify.toml` with base `next/`)
- **Backend**: your Ubuntu server (systemd file in `server/systemd/agentic.service`)

See detailed guide in this README below.
